Loan Committee members are paid $500 for each Management Loan Committee meeting attended and Ad-Hoc Committee members are paid $500 for each meeting attended</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Chairman does not receive per meeting fees or committee retainers.&nbsp;&nbsp;The CEO does not receive retainers or per meeting fees for Board or Board committee service</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Stock-based Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Corporation&#x2019;s 2014 Equity Incentive Plan (&#x201C;2014 Plan&#x201D;) allows for the granting of equity awards to non-employee directors of the Corporation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Equity compensation for directors consists of restricted stock units (&#x201C;RSUs&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;RSU awards for the Chairman and each non-employee director for 2019 service have been earned and will be granted after the 2020 Annual Meeting of Stockholders</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">10</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">RSUs </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">granted to non-employee directors in 2017 through 2019 are time-based RSUs that vest ratably and convert into shares of Common Stock over a three-year time period.&nbsp;&nbsp;All outstanding RSUs granted to directors immediately vest upon </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">retirement, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">an involuntary termination following a change in control, total and permanent disability or death</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Retirement Plan</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">On </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">June 18, 1991, the Board of the Bank adopted The First National Bank of Long Island Retirement Plan for Directors ("Retirement Plan").&nbsp;&nbsp;Effective December 31, 2000, benefits earned to date under the Retirement Plan were frozen and the ability of directors to earn additional benefits was discontinued.&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon retirement after attaining the age of sixty (60), each of the current directors who was a director prior to 2001 will receive a credit ("Credit Percentage") of ten percent (10%) multiplied by the number of years of service on the Board through December 31, 2000, not to exceed one hundred percent (100%).&nbsp;&nbsp;The annual benefit ("Annual Benefit") payable under the Retirement Plan is equal to the monthly Board of Directors&#x2019; attendance fee in effect as of December 31, 2000, which was $1,000, multiplied by twelve (12) and then multiplied by the Credit Percentage.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Annual Benefit is payable in quarterly installments for a period of seven (7) years from the date of retirement ("Payment Period").&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event of the death of a director or a retired director, the surviving spouse of such director is entitled to receive an annual payment equal to seventy-five percent (75%) of the Annual Benefit, calculated as set forth above, and payable over the remainder of the applicable Payment Period.&nbsp;&nbsp;Messrs. Canarick, Hogan and Teagle are the only directors participating in the Retirement Plan</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Mr. </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Becker joined the Board in January 2020 upon being named President and Chief Executive Officer of the Corporation and the Bank.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;Mr. Becker </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">has been employed by the Bank since 2011 most recently serving as Executive Vice President and Chief Risk Officer of the Corporation and the Bank and Corporate Secretary of the Corporation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Becker has been responsible for the Bank&#x2019;s enterprise risk management program including oversight of strategic planning, technology, loan and deposit operations, compliance, administration of internal audit, facilities and certain credit administration functions</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Mr. </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">McConie joined the Bank in 2015 and for the past five years was Senior Vice President and Chief Investment Officer.&nbsp;&nbsp;Effective January 1, 2020, Mr. McConie was promoted to Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of the Corporation and the Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;Prior to joining the Bank, Mr. McConie served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Community National Bank from 2007 to 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. McConie began his career at KPMG LLP in their Financial Services Group</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and is a Certified Public Accountant</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Mr. </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Hilton joined the Bank in June 2017 as Senior Vice President and Commercial Banking Division Executive.&nbsp;&nbsp;On January 1, 2018, Mr. Hilton was promoted to Executive Vice President of the Corporation and the Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;Prior to joining the Bank, Mr. Hilton served as Executive Vice President &amp; Chief Credit Officer of Suffolk County National Bank and its holding company, Suffolk Bancorp, until its acquisition by People&#x2019;s United Bank in April 2017.&nbsp; Mr. Hilton joined People&#x2019;s United Bank and served as Senior Credit Officer until May 2017.&nbsp; Prior to his employment at Suffolk County National Bank, Mr. Hilton served as Executive Vice President &amp; Chief Credit Officer of Empire National Bank and Vice President of its holding company, Empire Bancorp</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Ms. </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Verneuille joined the Bank in 2019 as Executive Vice President and Chief Risk Officer.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most recently Ms. Verneuille served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Empire National Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ms. Verneuille previously served as Director, Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of a national bank in organization after serving fifteen years at Bridgehampton National Bank, ultimately as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer. </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Ms. Verneuille is a Certified Public Accountant</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="Proposal2ApproveCompensationPaidtoNEOs"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">PROPOSAL 2</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">NON-BINDING, ADVISORY VOTE TO APPROVE THE COMPENSATION PAID TO THE </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">CORPORATION&#x2019;S NAMED EXECUTIVE OFFICERS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">compensation paid to our NEOs is disclosed in this proxy statement in the sections entitled &#x201C;Compensation Discussion and Analysis,&#x201D; &#x201C;Compensation of Executive Officers,&#x201D; &#x201C;Compensation Pursuant to Plans&#x201D; and &#x201C;Employment Agreements.&#x201D;&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that our compensation policies, practices and decisions are focused on pay-for-performance principles and are strongly aligned with the long-term best interests of our stockholders.&nbsp;&nbsp;Compensation of our NEOs is designed to enable us to attract and retain talented and experienced senior executives to lead the Corporation successfully in a competitive environment.&nbsp;&nbsp;Stockholders are being asked to cast a non-binding, advisory vote on the following resolution</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">:</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">RESOLVED, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">that the compensation paid to the Corporation&#x2019;s NEOs as disclosed in its proxy statement for the April 21, 2020 Annual Meeting of Stockholders pursuant to Item 402 of Regulation S-K, including the Compensation Discussion and Analysis, compensation tables and narrative discussion, is hereby APPROVED</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">12</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">affirmative vote of the holders of a majority of shares represented in person or by proxy and voting on this item will be required for approval</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Your </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">vote on this Proposal 2 is advisory, and therefore not binding on the Corporation, the Compensation Committee or the Board.&nbsp;&nbsp;The vote will not be construed to overrule any decision by the Corporation, the Compensation Committee or the Board; to create or imply any change to the fiduciary duties of the Corporation, the Compensation Committee or the Board; or to create or imply any additional fiduciary duties for the Corporation, the Compensation Committee or the Board.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, our Board and our Compensation Committee value the opinions of our stockholders and to the extent there is a significant vote against the compensation paid to our NEOs as disclosed in this proxy statement, we will consider our stockholders&#x2019; concerns and the Board and the Compensation Committee will evaluate whether any actions are necessary to address those concerns</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">The Board of Directors recommends a vote FOR the proposal to approve the</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">compensation paid to the Corporation&#x2019;s named executive officers.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="CompensationCommitteeReport"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">COMPENSATION COMMITTEE REPORT</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">We </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">have reviewed and discussed with management the Compensation Discussion and Analysis included herein and provided pursuant to Item 402(b) of Regulation S-K</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Based </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">on this review and discussion, we recommended to the Board that the Compensation Discussion and Analysis be included in this proxy statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Compensation Committee</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">:</font>
		</p>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 17.00pt;">
			<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">

			</p>
		</td><td style="width:19pt;"><p style="width:19pt;width:19pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Eric J. Tveter</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">, Chairman</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 17.00pt;">
			<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt;font-family:Symbol;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;font-size:10pt;;"> &#xB7;</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:19pt;"><p style="width:19pt;width:19pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">John J. Desmond</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 17.00pt;">
			<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt;font-family:Symbol;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;font-size:10pt;;"> &#xB7;</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:19pt;"><p style="width:19pt;width:19pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Stephen V. Murphy</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 17.00pt;">
			<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt;font-family:Symbol;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;font-size:10pt;;"> &#xB7;</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:19pt;"><p style="width:19pt;width:19pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Milbrey Rennie Taylor </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 17.00pt;">
			<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt 0pt 3pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 3pt;font-family:Symbol;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;font-size:10pt;;"> &#xB7;</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:19pt;"><p style="width:19pt;width:19pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt 0pt 3pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Walter C. Teagle III</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<p style="margin:3pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">preceding report shall not be deemed incorporated by reference by any general statement incorporating by reference this proxy statement into any filing under the Securities Act of 1933 (&#x201C;1933 Act&#x201D;) or the 1934 Act, except to the extent the Corporation specifically incorporates this information by reference, and shall not otherwise be deemed filed under the 1933 Act or the 1934 Act</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:center;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="CompensationDiscussionandAnalysis"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">COMPENSATION DISCUSSION AND ANALYSIS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">following is a discussion of the compensation awarded to, earned by or paid to the NEOs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The discussion explains all the material elements of the Corporation&#x2019;s compensation of the NEOs.&nbsp;&nbsp;It should be read in conjunction with the other executive compensation disclosures that appear elsewhere in this proxy statement</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Guiding Principles</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">In </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">designing and maintaining a compensation program for the Corporation&#x2019;s NEOs, other executive officers and employees, the Compensation Committee adheres to the following guiding principles</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">:</font>
		</p>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (1)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">compensation program should be principles-based, employ best practices in executive compensation and consider all relevant regulatory guidance regarding sound incentive compensation policies</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (2)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">compensation program should be designed and supervised by the Compensation Committee with, as needed, the assistance of independent compensation consultants, legal counsel and other advisors who have significant experience in risk management, compensation practices and legal matters in the financial services industry</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (3)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Compensation Committee should consist entirely of independent directors and operate under a charter adopted by the Board that clearly defines its duties and responsibilities.&nbsp;&nbsp;Significant approvals by the Compensation Committee regarding the provisions of the executive compensation program and awards thereunder should be ratified by the full Board</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (4)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">A &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">significant portion of executive compensation awarded under the program should be directly tied to corporate performance and thereby closely aligned with the interests of stockholders.&nbsp;&nbsp;The corporate performance levels necessary to earn threshold, target and maximum cash incentive and equity awards should be determined by the Compensation Committee and should not encourage inappropriate risks that could lead to material financial loss to the Bank</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (5)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">compensation program should enable the Corporation to attract and retain highly skilled professionals in each necessary discipline (i.e., executive, financial, lending, operations, risk </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">management).</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (6)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Compensation </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">paid should be appropriately balanced between short and long-term components.&nbsp;&nbsp;The short-term components should primarily consist of base salary and cash incentive compensation and the long-term components should be equity awards that vest over time as well as retirement benefits</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">13</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (7)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">competitiveness of total direct compensation, which consists of base salary, cash incentive and equity awards, should be tested regularly by a comparison to: (1) a group of peer banks selected by the Compensation Committee that are similar in size and scope to the Corporation; and (2) amounts published in compensation surveys for the banking industry conducted by nationally recognized independent compensation consulting firms</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (8)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">compensation program should achieve internal equity among the Corporation&#x2019;s executive officers</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (9)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Retirement </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">benefits should be market competitive and evaluated based on the percentage of the executive&#x2019;s income replaced in retirement</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (10)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Payments </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">upon a change in control or termination should be market competitive, reasonable in amount and designed to ensure that the executive officers of the Bank are not significantly harmed nor unduly enriched and are therefore objective with respect to the consummation of a transaction, such as a sale or merger of the Bank, that may be in the best interests of the Corporation&#x2019;s stockholders</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">. &nbsp;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (11)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Compensation Committee should identify those employees, whether they are executive officers or otherwise, who could potentially expose the Corporation to material amounts of risk.&nbsp;&nbsp;The compensation of such employees should be designed to discourage imprudent risk taking and contain maximum incentive amounts that do not represent windfalls</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (12)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Clawbacks </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">should be utilized within the compensation program in accordance with our clawback policy and applicable law</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (13)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Retention </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">of vested or exercised equity awards should be required until stock ownership guidelines are met</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.&nbsp; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (14)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Employees, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">whether they are executive officers or otherwise, should be prohibited from hedging the value of equity compensation that vests over time</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (15)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Performance </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">goals should be established by the Compensation Committee and ratified by the full Board</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (16)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Achievement </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">of performance goals should be certified by the Compensation Committee prior to the payment of awards</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Objectives of the Executive Compensation Program</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Corporation&#x2019;s executive compensation program is designed to enable the Corporation to attract and retain talented executive officers necessary to safely and successfully operate and grow the Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;The executive compensation program promotes sound risk management and long-term value creation for our stockholders</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">What the Executive Compensation Program is Designed to Reward</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Certain </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">elements of the executive compensation program are intended to reward current performance.&nbsp;&nbsp;By offering long-term equity compensation, the executive compensation program is also designed to reward executive officers who help maximize long-term financial performance and earnings growth of the Corporation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Elements of Executive Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">executive compensation program consists of four basic components: (1) base salary; (2) annual cash incentive compensation; (3) equity awards; and (4) other noncash compensation, consisting primarily of retirement benefits and reasonable perquisites</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Why We Choose To Pay Each Element of Executive Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-indent:18pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Base Salary.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> &nbsp;The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Compensation </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Committee believes that base salary for an NEO should compensate the officer for the skills and effort required to perform the officer&#x2019;s day-to-day responsibilities, taking into account the size and complexity of the Company</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-indent:18pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Annual </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Cash Incentive</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> Compensation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> &nbsp;The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Compensation Committee has included annual cash incentive compensation in the executive compensation program as a means to incent executive officers to optimize corporate performance through, among other things, the achievement of annual corporate goals set forth in the Corporation&#x2019;s strategic plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our Compensation Committee recommended, the Board adopted and the stockholders approved the 2016 Cash Incentive Plan, which provides the opportunity for a cash incentive payment based upon the achievement of corporate and individual goals</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-indent:18pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Equity Awards</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Compensation Committee uses equity awards granted under the Corporation&#x2019;s equity incentive plan as a means to incent executive officers to optimize corporate performance over an extended time-period.&nbsp;&nbsp;Equity awards, together with retirement benefits, are the longer-term components of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">our </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">executive compensation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> program</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:18pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#000000;">Other Noncash Compensation.</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;"> &nbsp;Other </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">noncash compensation consists of: (1) retirement benefits paid under the Bank&#x2019;s defined benefit pension plan (&#x201C;Pension Plan&#x201D;), 401(k) Plan and legacy Supplemental Executive Retirement Plan (&#x201C;SERP&#x201D;) that was applicable solely to the former CEO; and (2) noncash fringe benefits not available to the general employee population of the Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;Noncash fringe benefits, other than those available to the general employee population at the Bank, include the personal use of business automobiles and a country club membership for the CEO</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">14</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;">Retirement </font><font style="display: inline;">benefits provided by the Corporation&#x2019;s Pension and 401(k) Plans are intended to encourage the NEOs to maintain their employment with the Corporation and maximize long-term corporate performance.&nbsp;&nbsp;The SERP, of which the former CEO was the only participant, provided the additional pension and 401(k) benefits that the former CEO would receive in the absence of Internal Revenue Code provisions which limit the amount of compensation that can be considered in determining retirement benefits to be paid under the Bank&#x2019;s tax-qualified retirement plans.&nbsp;&nbsp;The SERP is explained in the &#x201C;PENSION BENEFITS&#x201D; section of this proxy statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;A country club membership is provided to the current CEO to aid him in developing and retaining business.&nbsp;&nbsp;Business automobiles are provided to all of the Bank&#x2019;s executive officers as a competitive perquisite and as an alternative to reimbursing such officers for mileage driven on account of business conducted on behalf of the Corporation</font><font style="display: inline;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">How We Determine The Amount To Pay For Each Element of Executive Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">total compensation paid by the Corporation to each of the NEOs is based on a variety of factors including: (1) the Company&#x2019;s recent and expected future overall financial performance; (2) current economic conditions and the effect thereof on the Company&#x2019;s performance and that of its peers; (3) the executive officer&#x2019;s experience and tenure in his or her current position, years of service to the Bank, scope of responsibilities, leadership ability, compensation relative to the Company&#x2019;s other executive officers, recent and expected future performance, and contributions to corporate performance; (4) a comparison of total compensation and each element of compensation paid to the executive to compensation amounts paid by peer banks to executives with similar roles and compensation amounts set forth in published industry surveys for executives with similar roles; and (5) the most recent stockholder advisory vote on executive compensation.&nbsp;&nbsp;As previously discussed, comparative compensation studies are performed and updated on a periodic basis by an independent compensation consulting firm engaged by and working under the direction of the Compensation Committee</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Base </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">salary for the CEO is reviewed by the Compensation Committee on an annual basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Compensation Committee also performs an annual review of the base salary recommendations made by the CEO for the Company&#x2019;s other NEOs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each executive officer does not necessarily receive an increase in base salary each year.&nbsp;&nbsp;In reviewing each NEO&#x2019;s base salary, the Compensation Committee considers the amounts paid by peer banks, the amounts set forth in compensation surveys performed by nationally recognized independent compensation consulting firms and the Corporation&#x2019;s overall budget for base salary increases.&nbsp;&nbsp;Regular annual salary increases for 2019 for the NEOs ranged from 3.5% to 7.7% with a weighted average 4.4%.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">For </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Corporation&#x2019;s </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">current and former </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">CEO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">former </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">CFO,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> annual</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> cash incentive compensation </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">payable pursuant to the 2016 Cash Incentive Plan </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">has been based on corporate performance measured by net income, return on assets (&#x201C;ROA&#x201D;) and bank safety and Compensation Committee discretion.&nbsp;&nbsp;Cash incentive compensation for the other NEOs has been based on a combination of corporate and personal performance with weights </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ranging from 8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">0% and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">2</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">0%, respectively, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">to 5</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">0% each.&nbsp;&nbsp;Corporate performance for the other NEOs is measured by net income, ROA, bank safety and Compensation Committee discretion, and personal performance is measured by the achievement of goals, monetary and nonmonetary, assigned to the NEO.&nbsp;&nbsp;Compensation Committee discretion is based on, among other things, a qualitative assessment of corporate performance in light of current conditions</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The </font><font style="display: inline;">following table sets forth the range of annual cash incentive compensation for 2019 under the 2016 Cash Incentive Plan assuming that the Corporation achieved threshold, target and maximum levels of performance and, where applicable, the NEO achieved threshold, target and maximum levels of performance with respect to personal goals.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each NEO&#x2019;s cash incentive target for 2019 was a percentage of base salary as determined by the Compensation Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;Achievement of corporate and, where applicable, personal performance levels greater than the threshold level but less than the maximum level results in a cash incentive payment that is proportionately greater than the threshold level of incentive but less than the maximum level of incentive</font><font style="display: inline;">.</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>

		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Equity </font><font style="display: inline;">incentive compensation for the NEOs consists of a combination of performance-based and time-based RSUs that are award based on a fixed percentage of salary as determined by the Compensation Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;RSUs awarded in 2018 and 2019 included two-thirds (&#x2154;) that were performance-based and one-third (&#x2153;) that were time-based.&nbsp;&nbsp;One-third (&#x2153;) vests and converts into shares of Common Stock based on the satisfaction of net income and ROA performance metrics for the year awarded, one-third (&#x2153;) vests and converts into shares of Common Stock based on the satisfaction of net income and ROA performance metrics for the year subsequent to the year awarded, and the final one-third (&#x2153;) vests and converts into shares of Common Stock three years from the date of grant.&nbsp;&nbsp;RSUs awarded in 2020 included two-thirds (&#x2154;) that are performance-based and one-third (&#x2153;) that are time-based.&nbsp;&nbsp;One-third (&#x2153;) vests and converts into shares of Common Stock based on the Corporation&#x2019;s ROE and ROA compared to the 2019 peer group median each with a weighting of 40% and net income growth with a weighting of 20% for the year awarded, (&#x2153;) vests and converts into shares of Common Stock based on the Corporation&#x2019;s ROE and ROA compared to the 2019 peer group median each with a weighting of 40% and net income </font>
		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">15</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;">growth with a weighting of 20% for the year subsequent to the year awarded, and the final one-third (&#x2153;) vests and converts three years from the date of grant.&nbsp;&nbsp;Multi-year performance periods for the performance-based RSUs encourage long-term strategic focus</font><font style="display: inline;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">P</font><font style="display: inline;">erformance-based </font><font style="display: inline;">RSUs granted in 2018, 2019 and 2020 have upside conversion potential in that a maximum level of performance will result in the distribution of more than one share of Common Stock for one RSU.&nbsp;&nbsp;A maximum level of performance will result in a conversion ratio of one RSU for one-and-one-half (1&#xBD;) shares of Common Stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;Performance greater than the threshold level but less than the maximum level will result in a conversion ratio proportionately greater than one RSU for one-half (&#xBD;) share of Common Stock but less than one RSU for one-and-one-half (1&#xBD;) shares of Common Stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;The maximum level of performance is 115% of the target level, whereas the threshold level of performance is 80% of the target level.&nbsp;&nbsp;In setting the current threshold, target and maximum levels of performance and related payouts, the Compensation Committee utilized the study performed by </font><font style="display: inline;">Pearl Meyer </font><font style="display: inline;">of the structural elements of the Corporation&#x2019;s incentive compensation plan and considered, among other things, performance and payout levels for the Corporation&#x2019;s peer banks</font><font style="display: inline;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Over </font><font style="display: inline;">the last three years, cash incentive compensation for the NEOs as a group has averaged approximately one-third (&#x2153;) of total incentive compensation, while equity incentive compensation has averaged approximately two-thirds (&#x2154;) of total incentive compensation</font><font style="display: inline;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">By </font><font style="display: inline;">their terms, all outstanding performance-based RSUs held by NEOs immediately vest in the event of an involuntary termination following a change in control, total and permanent disability, as defined, or death.&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon retirement performance-based RSUs will vest only after the completion of the applicable performance period and attainment of the relevant performance criteria.&nbsp;&nbsp;All outstanding time-based RSUs granted to NEOs immediately vest in the event of an involuntary termination following a change in control, total and permanent disability, as defined, death or retirement.&nbsp;&nbsp;For a further discussion of the tax-deductibility of executive compensation, see the Tax Deductibility of Executive Compensation section of this proxy statement</font><font style="display: inline;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">value of a RSU realized at vesting can be more or less than its grant date fair value if the Common Stock price at the date of vesting is more or less than its fair market value on the date of grant or the aggregate conversion ratio described above is more or less than one RSU for one share of Common Stock</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
