		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;">The </font><font style="display: inline;">Compensation Committee believes that total target remuneration for executive officers should be market competitive, benchmarked to the 50</font><font style="display: inline;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">th</font><font style="display: inline;"> percentile of the Bank&#x2019;s peer group and take into consideration individual and corporate performance and tenure</font><font style="display: inline;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">In </font><font style="display: inline;">performing their 2019 review of executive compensation, </font><font style="display: inline;">Pearl Meyer </font><font style="display: inline;">compiled compensation data from the proxy statements of the Corporation&#x2019;s custom peer group and from published industry surveys and, based on this data, calculated percentile amounts against which total compensation for the Company&#x2019;s NEOs could be compared.&nbsp;&nbsp;The </font><font style="display: inline;">Pearl Meyer </font><font style="display: inline;">study showed that total target compensation for all NEOs ranged from the 12</font><font style="display: inline;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">th</font><font style="display: inline;"> to the 78</font><font style="display: inline;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">th</font><font style="display: inline;"> percentile</font><font style="display: inline;">.</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Termination and Change in Control Payments</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Each </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">of the NEOs ha</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">d</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> an employment agreement with the Corporation </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">during 2019, which </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">provides for severance compensation in the event that the executive is terminated by the Board without cause or terminates his employment for Good Reason, as defined, whether or not such termination occurs in connection with a change in control (see Employment Agreements section of this proxy statement).&nbsp;&nbsp;These provisions are designed to insure, among other things, that the NEOs are not significantly harmed or unduly enriched and are therefore objective with respect to the consummation of a transaction, such as a sale or merger of the Bank that may be in the best interests of the Corporation&#x2019;s stockholders.&nbsp;&nbsp;In determining the severance arrangement for the CEO and each of the other NEOs, the Compensation Committee considered the severance arrangements offered by peer banks to their NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Impact of Accounting and Tax Treatment of Certain Elements of Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">T</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">he </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Compensation Committee has granted non-qualified stock options (&#x201C;NQSOs&#x201D;) and RSUs as equity compensation.&nbsp;&nbsp;NQSOs and RSUs are advantageous from the Corporation&#x2019;s standpoint because the Corporation records a book tax benefit for the compensation cost recognized for financial statement reporting purposes under FASB ASC Topic 718</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;U</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">pon exercise of NQSOs and vesting of RSUs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the Corporation records an income tax benefit or expense in earnings</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Tax Deductibility of Executive Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Internal </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Revenue Code Section 162(m) limits the tax deductibility of compensation paid to any covered employee to $1 million per year.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Tax Cuts and Jobs Act (the &#x201C;Act&#x201D;) was signed into law on December 22, 2017 and amends Section 162(m) to treat all NEOs as covered employees (previously the CFO was not a covered employee) and to eliminate the exclusion of qualified performance-based compensation in determining compensation subject to the $1 million limitation.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, the Act provides &#x201C;grandfathered&#x201D; treatment for qualified performance-based compensation in excess of $1 million that meets the requirements of Section 162(m), is payable pursuant to a written binding contract in effect as of November 2, 2017 and is not modified in any material respect.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most of the compensation paid to the NEOs as a group through year-end 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> was deductible under the applicable provisions of Section 162(m).&nbsp;&nbsp;A number of requirements must be met for particular compensation to qualify for tax deductibility, so there can be no assurance that incentive compensation paid to the NEOs will be fully deductible in all circumstances</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">While </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the Compensation Committee does not have a formal policy with respect to the payment of compensation in excess of the deduction limit under Code Section 162(m), the Compensation Committee&#x2019;s practice is to structure compensation programs offered to the NEOs with a view towards maximizing tax deductibility of amounts paid.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, in structuring compensation programs, the Compensation Committee considers a variety of factors, including the Corporation&#x2019;s tax position, the materiality of the payments and tax deductions involved and the need for flexibility to address unforeseen circumstances.&nbsp;&nbsp;After considering these factors, the Compensation Committee may decide to authorize payments, all or part of which may be nondeductible for federal income tax purposes</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Role of Executive Officers In Determining Executive Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Compensation Committee approves the proposed compensation of executive officers after considering, among other things, executive compensation studies periodically performed by independent compensation consulting firms.&nbsp;&nbsp;From time to time, the CEO and CFO have served as a resource to the Compensation Committee in gathering the information necessary to make such compensation determinations.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, these officers do not have a policy-making role with respect to determining the amount or form of executive compensation and do not participate in Compensation Committee deliberations regarding their own compensation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Compensation Policies and Practices As They Relate To Risk Management</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Corporation has a written incentive-based compensation policy that sets forth governance roles for the Compensation Committee, senior management and the Corporation&#x2019;s internal auditors.&nbsp;&nbsp;The policy is reviewed annually by the Compensation Committee, modified if deemed appropriate and approved.&nbsp;&nbsp;The purpose of the policy is to ensure that the Corporation&#x2019;s incentive-based compensation arrangements, or any feature of any such arrangement, do not encourage executive officers or employees to: (1) expose the Corporation to inappropriate risks by providing such persons with excessive compensation, fees or benefits; or (2) take inappropriate risks that could lead to material financial loss to the Corporation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Pursuant to this policy, the Corporation&#x2019;s incentive-based compensation arrangements are required to: (1) balance risk and financial rewards, through such things as risk adjustments of awards, deferral of payments, longer performance periods and/or reduced sensitivity to short-term performance; (2) be compatible with effective internal controls and risk management; and (3) be supported by strong corporate governance, including active and effective oversight by the Compensation </font>
		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">17</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Compensation Committee has determined that the Company&#x2019;s compensation policies and practices for its employees, including non-executive officers, are not reasonably likely to have a material adverse effect on the Company</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Stock Ownership Guidelines</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;"> and Equity Award Retention Policy</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">As</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">a condition to receiving equity awarded under the Corporation&#x2019;s equity incentive plan each director and executive officer shall enter into an agreement with the Company providing that any stock acquired from the exercise of stock options or the vesting of equity awards, net of the disposition of shares for tax withholding requirements, must be held until stock ownership requirements are met</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Each </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">director of the Corporation is required to have beneficial ownership of shares of Common Stock of the Corporation with a current market value equal to three (3) times cash retainers, which includes Committee retainers and per meeting fees.&nbsp;&nbsp;The CEO of the Corporation is required to have beneficial ownership of shares of common stock of the Corporation with a current market value equal to three (3) times his or her current base salary.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each other executive officer of the Corporation is required to have beneficial ownership of shares of common stock of the Corporation with a current market value equal to one (1) times his or her current base salary.&nbsp;&nbsp;All ownership requirements need to be met as follows: (1) within five years of becoming a director or executive officer; (2) within five years of an increase in ownership requirements for the incremental increase only; or (3) within three years of falling out of compliance with these requirements due to compensation increases or fluctuations in market value</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Clawback Policy</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The </font><font style="display: inline;">Corporation has a clawback policy to enable the Company to recover any bonus or incentive compensation awarded or paid to the Company&#x2019;s executive officers if: (1) the payments or awards were based on materially inaccurate financial statements or any other materially inaccurate performance metric, and (2) the amount of the incentive compensation, as calculated under restated financial results, is less than the amount actually paid or awarded under the original financial results</font><font style="display: inline;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Policy Prohibiting </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Hedging</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">, Margining and Pledging of the Corporation&#x2019;s Securities</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Directors, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">NEOs, other officers and employees are prohibited from hedging the Corporation&#x2019;s securities with the use of financial instruments (including prepaid variable forward contracts, equity swaps, calls, puts, collars, and exchange funds) that offset a decrease in the market value of the Company&#x2019;s equity securities and any other transaction with comparable economic consequences.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Directors, NEOs </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">other </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">executive </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">officers are </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">also </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">prohibited</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, with limited exception,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> from</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">hold</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ing</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the Corporation&#x2019;s </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">securities in a margin account or pledg</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ing</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">such </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">securities as collateral for any loan</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Shareholder </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Advisory Vote on Compensation and Policy </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Prohibiting </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Tax Gross-Up Arrangements</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Compensation Committee considers the results of the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">most recent </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">annual </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">stockholder </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">say-on-pay advisory vote on the compensation paid to NEOs.&nbsp;&nbsp;To the extent there is a significant vote against the compensation paid to our NEOs, the Compensation Committee will consider our stockholders&#x2019; concerns and evaluate whether any actions are necessary to address those concerns.&nbsp;&nbsp;At the 2019 Annual Meeting of Stockholders, 69% </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">of the shares voting on this issue </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">support</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ed</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the compensation outlined in last year&#x2019;s proxy statement, while 31% voted against or abstained.&nbsp;&nbsp;After a review of the say-on-pay advisory vote results, it was determined that the Corporation&#x2019;s legacy tax gross-up arrangement provided to the former President and CEO contributed substantially to the voting results.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Compensation Committee determined that n</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">o &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">significant </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">revisions were necessary to our executive compensation program because the Board has a longstanding prohibition against tax gross-up arrangements which is published in the Corporation&#x2019;s Corporate Governance Guidelines</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the sole individual receiving such a gross-up payment is now retired</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and the compensation program under which the tax gross-up payment was made has expired</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="CompensationofExecutiveOfficers"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">COMPENSATION OF EXECUTIVE OFFICERS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">following table sets forth information with respect to the aggregate compensation paid, earned or awarded for the years ended December 31, 2019, 2018 and 2017 to the CEO, CFO and each of the additional three most highly compensated executive officers of the Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;All compensation information is provided pursuant to the SEC executive compensation disclosure rules for proxy statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;All of the listed officers are also officers of the Corporation but received salaries only from the Bank</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">18</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

						&nbsp;</p>
				</td>

				<td valign="bottom" style="width:15.84%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000 ;border-right:1pt solid #000000 ;background-color: #CCEEFF;height:13.10pt;padding:0pt 6.5pt">
					<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
						<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">8,400</font></p>
				</td>
				<td valign="bottom" style="width:14.16%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000 ;border-right:1pt solid #000000 ;background-color: #CCEEFF;height:13.10pt;padding:0pt 6.5pt">
					<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
						<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">16,231</font></p>
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;">
				<sup style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;text-decoration:none;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;text-decoration:none;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;;"> (1)</sup>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Bank ha</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">d</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> a legacy SERP for the former CEO that is explained in the &#x201C;P</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">ENSION </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">B</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">ENEFITS</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&#x201D; section of this proxy statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;The former CEO&#x2019;s participation in the legacy SERP began upon his tenure as CEO of the Corporation and the Bank in 2004.&nbsp;&nbsp;Except for this one legacy SERP, the Board has adopted a prohibition of tax gross-up arrangements and has included this prohibition in the Corporation&#x2019;s published Corporate Governance Guidelines</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Compensation Committee believes that each NEO&#x2019;s total compensation is appropriately balanced between currently paid out and deferred compensation, with deferred compensation consisting of equity awards that vest over time and retirement benefits provided under the Corporation&#x2019;s 401(k), Pension and SERP plans</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Pay Ratio</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Pursuant </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">to Item 402(u) of Regulation S-K and Section 953(b) of the Dodd-Frank Act, presented below is the ratio of annual total compensation of the Corporation&#x2019;s former CEO to the annual total compensation of the Corporation&#x2019;s median paid employee, excluding the former CEO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">ratio presented below is a reasonable estimate calculated in a manner consistent with Item 402(u).</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Corporation utilized the same median paid employee for 2017, 2018 and 2019.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Corporation believes this is appropriate because there have not been significant changes in the employee population or compensation arrangements</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">In </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">identifying the median paid employee in 2017 and in determining the compensation of the median paid employee in each year, the Corporation utilized year-to-date compensation from the final (twenty-sixth) bi-weekly payroll paid in December of each year.&nbsp;&nbsp;Compensation included, as applicable, regular earnings plus overtime, Saturday pay, commissions, cash incentives and stock-based compensation.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Corporation considered all full-time and part-time permanent employees when identifying the median paid employee in 2017.&nbsp;&nbsp;Earnings of employees included on the final payroll of 2017 that were employed for less than a full year were converted to a twenty-six bi-weekly payroll equivalent. Full-time equivalent adjustments were not made. There were no seasonal or temporary employees on the final payroll of 2017</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">2019 annual total compensation of the CEO and median paid employee was determined under Item 402 of Regulation S-K and was $1,978,809 and $78,759, respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;The CEO&#x2019;s annual total compensation for 2019 was 25 times that of the annual total compensation for 2019 of the median paid employee.&nbsp;&nbsp;This compares to 2018 annual total compensation of $1,891,844 and $60,496, respectively, and a 2018 pay ratio of 31 times</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="CompensationPursuanttoPlans"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">COMPENSATION PURSUANT TO PLANS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;">Equity Incentive Plans </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Corporation has awards outstanding under the 2006 Stock Compensation Plan (&#x201C;2006 Plan&#x201D;) and the 2014 Plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;Currently, awards can only be granted under the 2014 Plan, which was approved by the Corporation&#x2019;s stockholders on April 22, 2014 as a successor to the 2006 Plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;The 2014 Plan gives the Board flexibility to attract and retain highly qualified officers and directors by offering a competitive compensation program.&nbsp;&nbsp;Equity awards align the interests of our directors and management with the interests of our stockholders by potentially increasing the ownership interests of directors and officers in our Common Stock</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Awards </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">under the 2014 Plan may be granted as incentive and non-qualified stock options, stock appreciation rights, restricted stock awards, restricted stock units or any combination thereof.&nbsp;&nbsp;Substantially all awards granted under the 2014 Plan have been restricted stock units with performance or time-based vesting, while awards granted under the predecessor plan consisted of a combination of nonqualified stock options and restricted stock units</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">following table presents the number of shares of Common Stock to be issued upon the exercise of outstanding stock options and vesting of RSUs, and the number of shares of Common Stock remaining available for future issuance under the 2014 Plan, as of </font>
		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">20</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Includes </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">325,644 RSUs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The weighted-average exercise price does not take these awards into account</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.&nbsp; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>

			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">these </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">shares, 1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">90</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">879</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> are available to be granted as restricted stock or RSUs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Corporation does not have any equity compensation plans that have not been approved by stockholders</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">amounts shown represent RSU awards earned by the NEOs for 2019 service.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amounts earned were awarded in December 2019 and January 2020 in the form of RSUs under the 2014 Plan and are included in the &#x201C;Stock Awards&#x201D; column for 2019 of the &#x201C;Summary Compensation Table&#x201D; in this proxy statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;Two-thirds (&#x2154;) of the RSUs granted in December 2019 and January 2020 are performance-based and one-third (&#x2153;) are time-based.&nbsp;&nbsp;One-third (&#x2153;) vests and converts into shares of Common Stock based on the Corporation&#x2019;s ROE and ROA compared to the 2019 peer group median each with a weighting of 40% and net income growth with a weighting of 20% for the year awarded, (&#x2153;) vests and converts into shares of Common Stock based on the Corporation&#x2019;s ROE and ROA compared to the 2019 peer group median each with a weighting of 40% and net income growth with a weighting of 20% for the year subsequent to the year awarded, and the final one-third (&#x2153;) vests and converts three years from the date of grant</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> but is subject to earlier vesting and conversion based on the retirement of the grantee</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>

		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;">
				<sup style="margin:6pt 0pt 3pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (1)</sup>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">actuarial assumptions used in determining the present value of the accumulated benefit for each NEO under the Pension Plan are set forth in Note J &#x201C;Retirement Plans&#x201D; to the Corporation&#x2019;s 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> Consolidated Financial Statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;With respect to the SERP, the present value of the accumulated benefit is equal to the estimated present value of the annuity on </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">December 3</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">1, 2019</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Pension Plan</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Employees, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">including the NEOs, who are over 21 years of age and have been employed by the Bank for more than one year, are eligible to participate in the Pension Plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;Compensation used to determine benefits includes base salary, commissions, cash incentive compensation and taxable fringe benefits, but excludes employer contributions to the 401(k) Plan, amounts realized from the exercise of nonqualified stock options, amounts realized from the conversion of restricted stock units into shares of stock and amounts realized from the sale, exchange or other disposition of stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employees that elect to participate in the Pension Plan make contributions of 2% of their compensation used to determine benefits.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employees become fully vested in the Pension Plan after 5 years of service with the Bank and 4 years of participation in the Pension Plan (no vesting occurs during that 5-year period) or, for employees hired before February 28, 2011, upon attainment of age 55.&nbsp;&nbsp;The normal retirement age is 65.&nbsp;&nbsp;For benefits earned through February 28, 2011, early retirement with an unreduced benefit is available at age 62, provided that at least 10 years of vesting service had been completed by age 62 and employment by the Bank began at age 55 or prior.&nbsp;&nbsp;Early retirement with a reduced benefit is available beginning at age 55.&nbsp;&nbsp;For benefits earned through February 28, 2011, the reduction is equal to 3% per year for each year that early retirement precedes age 65, or age 62 provided that at least 10 years of vesting service have been completed by age 62 and employment began at age 55 or prior.&nbsp;&nbsp;For benefits earned after February 28, 2011, the reduction is based on actuarial equivalence</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Upon </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">retirement, each participant with a spouse is paid a benefit in the form of a joint and survivor annuity.&nbsp;&nbsp;Participants without a spouse are paid a benefit in the form of a single life annuity guaranteed for sixty (60) months.&nbsp;&nbsp;All participants, whether with or without a spouse, may elect optional forms of benefit payments.&nbsp;&nbsp;For all participants, the annuity benefit is an amount equal to the sum of: (1) the participant&#x2019;s Average Annual Compensation multiplied by the product of 1.75 percent and the participant&#x2019;s credited years of service through February 28, 2011; plus (2) the participant&#x2019;s Average Annual Compensation multiplied by the product of 1.50 percent and the participant&#x2019;s credited years of service after February 28, 2011, with total years of credited service under clauses &#x201C;1&#x201D; and &#x201C;2&#x201D; limited to a maximum of 35 years; plus (3) 1.25 percent of Average Annual Compensation multiplied by the participant&#x2019;s credited years of service in excess of 35 years (up to five such years); and less (4) the product of .49 percent of the participant&#x2019;s Final Average Annual Compensation, limited to Covered Compensation, and the participant&#x2019;s Benefit Service up to 35 years.&nbsp;&nbsp;The 0.49 percent represents the minimum Social Security offset to the pension benefit.&nbsp;&nbsp;Average Annual Compensation, Final Average Annual Compensation, Covered Compensation and Benefit Service are all as defined in the Plan document</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Supplemental Executive Retirement Plan</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Corporation has no active supplemental executive retirement plans.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board of Directors has adopted a prohibition of tax gross-up arrangements for such plans and included this prohibition in the Corporation&#x2019;s published Corporate Governance Guidelines</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">Bank had a legacy SERP with the Corporation&#x2019;s former CEO as its only participant.&nbsp;&nbsp;The SERP provided the additional benefits that would have been provided to the former CEO under the Pension and 401(k) Plans in the absence of Internal Revenue Code limitations for qualified plans.&nbsp;&nbsp;The SERP was also designed so that the supplemental pension and 401(k) contributions were made to a "secular trust" for the benefit of the former CEO so that the assets were protected in the same manner as those of the Pension and 401(k) Plans (amounts contributed to the secular trust were not subject to the claims of creditors of the Bank).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Bank&#x2019;s contributions to the secular trust were tax-deductible by the Bank when made and taxable to the former CEO when received or earned by the trust.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Bank&#x2019;s contributions to the SERP were reduced by applicable income tax withholdings of the former CEO.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result of the foregoing, the Bank contributed an amount to the SERP that, after applicable withholding taxes, was sufficient to fund the SERP&#x2019;s benefit obligation when due.&nbsp;&nbsp;The assets in the secular trust were invested in equity and fixed income mutual funds, which produced earnings from dividends and interest</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">23</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

					<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
						<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">in Last Fiscal Year </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">(1)</font></p>
				</td>
				<td valign="bottom" style="width:26.62%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt solid #000000 ;background-color: #auto;height:13.10pt;padding:0pt 6.5pt">

		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;color:#000000;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:3pt 0pt 0pt;">
				<sup style="margin:3pt 0pt;line-height:100%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;color:#000000;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (3)</sup>

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">Includes </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">$100,169 previously reported as compensation to the NEO in the Summary Compensation Tables for previous years</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">401(k) Plan</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Bank has a tax-qualified 401(k) Plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employees, including the NEOs, are eligible to participate provided they are at least 18 years of age.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Bank may, at its sole discretion, make matching contributions to each participant's account based on the amount of the participant's tax deferred contributions.&nbsp;&nbsp;Eligibility for employer matching contributions, if any, occurs after completing twelve (12) consecutive months of Eligibility Service, as defined, in which the participant worked a minimum of 1,000 hours.&nbsp;&nbsp;The sum of employee elective contributions and employer matching contributions plus any other additions to a participant&#x2019;s account for 2019 cannot exceed the lesser of $55,000 or 100% of the participant&#x2019;s compensation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Participants are fully vested in their elective contributions and fully vest in any employer matching contributions after five years of participation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employer matching contributions made during the first five years of participation vest ratably over the remainder of the five-year period</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Participants </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">in the 401(k) Plan will receive benefits generally upon attainment of age 65.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, the 401(k) Plan contains provisions allowing pre-termination withdrawals and loans under certain circumstances.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amount of a participant&#x2019;s Normal Retirement Benefit, as defined, will depend upon the accumulation of contributions and forfeitures and the investment performance of the 401(k) Plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;The 401(k) Plan matching contributions for 2019 made to the account of each NEO are set forth in the &#x201C;All Other Compensation Table&#x201D; appearing elsewhere in this proxy statement</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="EmploymentAgreement"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">E</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">MPLOYMENT AGREEMENTS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">NEOs each have or have had employment agreements with the Corporation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Vittorio&#x2019;s employment agreement expired in</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> accordance with its terms as of December 31, 2019 and the Corporation has no further obligations thereunder.&nbsp;&nbsp;Messrs. Curtis and</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Daley agreed to retire from employment with the Corporation and the Bank effective January 1, 2020.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">The parties agreed that </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">for purposes </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">of their employment agreements, the retirements </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">would </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">be considered a termination of employment without cause.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;"> The Company and the Bank entered into</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;"> separate</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;"> retirement agreements with Messrs. Curtis and Daley as of January 1, 2020 (the &#x201C;Retirement Agreements&#x201D;), under which the</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">ir employment agreements terminated, the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">Bank</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">pa</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">id</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;"> $865,262 to Mr. Curtis and $930,816 to Mr. Daley in a cash lump sum to settle any outstanding contractual obligations</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;"> and</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;"> the Company</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;"> transfer</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">red</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;"> ownership to Messrs. Curtis and Daley of their company-issued automobiles.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;"> The Retirement Agreement with Mr. Curtis include</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">d</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;"> certain consulting services to be provided by Mr. Curtis for the twelve month period following his retirement, for which he will be compensated $135,000</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Mr.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Hilton&#x2019;s employment agreement has a term of two (2) calendar years beginning January 1, 2018.&nbsp;&nbsp;Commencing on the first anniversary of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">employment agreement and continuing on each anniversary thereafter, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">agreement renew</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> for an additional period of one year such that the remaining term shall be two years unless written notice of non-renewal is provided at least thirty (30) days prior to any such anniversary date.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> employment agreement expire</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> on December 31 of the calendar year in which </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Mr. Hilton </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">attains age 65 (&#x201C;Retirement Age Termination Date&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;Nothing in the employment agreement mandate</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> or prohibit</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> employment of the NEO beyond th</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">e</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> Retirement Age Termination Dates.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Mr. Hilton </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">shall not be entitled to any benefits or payments under his employment agreement following the Retirement Age Termination Date unless the Corporation has elected to extend such agreement pursuant to its terms for an additional period of two years.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">If </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">he </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">is terminated by the Board without cause or if he terminates his employment following an event constituting Good Reason, he will receive a cash lump sum severance payment equal to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">two</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;"> times base salary plus an amount equal to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">twenty-four</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;"> times the product of the monthly cost of insurance coverage maintained by the Bank for the executive immediately prior to the date of termination.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">The cash lump sum payment is conditioned on the executive executing a release of claims against the Company and any affiliate, and their officers, directors, successors and assigns.&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon termination of employment without cause or with Good Reason by the executive on or after a change in control, the executive shall receive a cash lump sum payment equal to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">two</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;"> times the sum of the highest rate of base salary payable during the calendar year of termination or either of the two calendar years immediately preceding the date of termination. </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">In addition, the executive shall receive a cash lump sum equal to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">twenty-four</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;"> times the monthly cost of insurance coverage maintained by the Bank for the executive immediately prior to the date of termination</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">March 2019, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">t</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">he Co</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">rporation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;"> and the Bank entered into a new employment agreement with Mr. Becker, effective January 1, 2020, with terms substantially similar to the employment agreement to which Mr. Vittorio </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">was </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">a party. Th</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">is</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;"> employment agreement has a term of three calendar years beginning January 1, 2020 and may be renewed annually for an additional year</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">upon </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">written notice of renewal</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">The initial base salary is $500,000. If the</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">executive is terminated by the Board without cause or if he terminates his employment following an event constituting Good Reason, he will receive a cash lump sum severance payment equal to three times base salary plus an amount equal to thirty-six times the product of the monthly cost of insurance coverage maintained by the Bank for the executive immediately prior to the date of termination.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">The cash lump sum payment is conditioned on the executive executing a release of claims against the Company and any affiliate, and their officers, directors, successors and assigns.&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon termination of employment without cause or with Good Reason by the executive on or after a change in control, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">Mr. Becker</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;"> shall receive a cash lump sum payment equal to three times the sum of the highest rate of base salary payable during the calendar year of termination or either of the two calendar </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">years immediately preceding the date of termination.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, the executive shall receive a cash lump sum equal to thirty-six times the monthly cost of insurance coverage maintained by the Bank for the executive immediately prior to the date of termination</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">Notwithstanding </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">the foregoing, the change in control severance payments under the employment agreements for the NEOs will be reduced to avoid an excess parachute payment under Section 280G of the Internal Revenue Code if doing so results in a greater after-tax benefit to the NEO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">Each </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">NEO&#x2019;s employment agreement subjects the NEO to non-compete and non-solicitation provisions for a period of two years for the CEO or one year for the other NEOs following their date of termination, provided, however, that such restrictions would not apply in the event of the NEOs termination for cause or termination of employment following a change in control</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 3pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;">tables below set forth potential payments to Messrs. Becker and Hilton upon termination of their employment by the Corporation without cause or by the NEOs for Good Reason absent a change in control and following a change in control.&nbsp;&nbsp;The tables also set forth for the NEOs the accelerated</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> vesting, if any, of unvested option and stock awards. </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">All outstanding and unvested equity awards for the NEOs by their terms will immediately vest upon a </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">termination of employment following </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">change in control.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;The amounts shown in the table below do not take into account any reduction in payments required to comply with Section 280G of the Code.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Information is not provided below for Messrs. Vittorio, Curtis and Daley because their employment agreements have been terminated and the Corporation has no further obligations thereunder.&nbsp;&nbsp;Payments made to Messrs. Curtis and Daley in exchange for the termination of their employment </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">agreements are described above</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>

					<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<div style="width:100%"><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse:collapse;width: 100.00%;margin-left:0pt;">
