		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Corporation&#x2019;s Corporate Governance Guidelines require the Board to conduct an appropriate review of all related party transactions for potential conflict of interest situations.&nbsp;&nbsp;Related party transactions are those required to be disclosed pursuant to Item 404 of Regulation S-K.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board fulfills the requirement to review related party transactions in conjunction with the Audit Committee, which is comprised entirely of independent directors.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Governance and Nominating Committee is charged with the responsibility of </font>
		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">25</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">reviewing and assessing the adequacy of and compliance with the Corporation&#x2019;s Corporate Governance Guidelines and recommending any proposed changes to the Board for approval</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="_Hlk536695321"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">1992, the Bank, as tenant, entered into a lease with H. T. Hogan Jr., d/b/a Briar Ridge Properties, covering premises in a building located in Locust Valley, New York, used as a branch office.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Bank subsequently modified and extended the lease in 2002 and 2012.&nbsp;&nbsp;The 2012 modification and extension, including the current five-year renewal period</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> which began in 2017</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, expires on October 31, 2022.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to base rent, the Bank is responsible for its proportionate share of the real estate taxes on the building in which the leased premises are located.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under the terms of the lease, the Bank was obligated to pay $44,389 for the year ended December 31, 2019.&nbsp;&nbsp;In 2009, the Bank, as tenant, entered into a lease with CSH Realty LLC, covering premises in a building located in Cold Spring Harbor, New York used as a branch office.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Bank subsequently extended the lease </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">for five years effective January 1, 2020 and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">expir</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ing </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">on December 31, 2024.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under the terms of the lease, the Bank was obligated to pay $33,014 for the year ended December 31, 2019.&nbsp;&nbsp;Howard Thomas Hogan, Jr., a director of the Corporation and the Bank, owns or controls companies that own both properties.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Corporation believes that the terms of the leases are comparable to competitive terms that could have been obtained from an unrelated third party</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Bank has had, and expects to have in the future, banking transactions in the ordinary course of its business with directors, executive officers, principal stockholders of the Corporation and their associates.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such transactions, including borrowings and loan commitments, are made in the ordinary course of business on substantially the same terms, including interest rates and collateral, as those prevailing at the time for comparable transactions with others and, in the opinion of management, do not involve more than a normal risk of collectability nor do they present other unfavorable features</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Certain </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">directors are officers, directors, partners or stockholders of companies or partnerships which, or associates of which, may have been customers of the Bank in the ordinary course of business during 2019 and up to the present time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additional transactions of this type may occur in the future.&nbsp;&nbsp;All such transactions were effected on substantially the same terms as comparable transactions with other persons</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="Section16A"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">DELINQUENT </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">SECTION&nbsp;16(A) REPORT</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">S</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Our </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">executive </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">officers, directors and beneficial owners of greater than 10% of the outstanding shares of Common Stock are required to file reports with the SEC disclosing beneficial ownership and changes in beneficial ownership of our Common Stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;SEC rules require disclosure if an executive officer, director or 10% beneficial owner does not file these reports on a timely basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on our review of ownership reports required to be filed for the year ended December 31, 2019, all filing requirements were satisfied on a timely basis except for one Form 4 filing for each of Directors Peter Quick and Denise Strain relating to shares received in lieu of director fees.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Corporation, on behalf of each director, inadvertently filed each Form 4 four business days late on October 28, 2019</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="Proposal3AppointmentofPublicAcctFirm"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">PROPOSAL </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">3</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">RATIFICATION OF APPOINTMENT OF INDEPENDENT REGISTERED</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">consolidated financial statements of the Corporation for the year ended December 31, 2019 were audited by Crowe LLP (&#x201C;Crowe&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Audit Committee has appointed Crowe as the Corporation&#x2019;s independent registered public accounting firm to audit the Corporation&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements for the year ending December 31, 2020.&nbsp;&nbsp;A resolution will be presented at the Annual Meeting of Stockholders to ratify the appointment of Crowe.&nbsp;&nbsp;The affirmative vote of the holders of a majority of shares represented in person or by proxy and voting on this item will be required for ratification.&nbsp;&nbsp;If there is no designation on an executed proxy as to how the shares represented should be voted, the proxy will be voted for the ratification.&nbsp;&nbsp;If the stockholders do not ratify the appointment of Crowe, the Audit Committee will reconsider its selection of Crowe as the Corporation&#x2019;s independent registered public accounting firm.&nbsp;&nbsp;Even if the stockholders ratify the appointment of Crowe, the Audit Committee in its discretion may direct the appointment of a different independent registered public accounting firm </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">at any time during the year if it determines that such change is in the best interests of the Corporation and its stockholders</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">A &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">representative of Crowe is expected to be present at the Annual Meeting of Stockholders and will have the opportunity to make a statement and respond to appropriate questions from stockholders</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">The Board of Directors recommends a vote FOR ratification of the appointment of Crowe as the Corporation&#x2019;s independent registered public accounting firm.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">26</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Audit Fees </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Crowe</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&#x2019;s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">fees for audit services for 2019 and 2018 were $430,000 and $305,000, respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;The increase in audit fees is mainly due to audit work totaling $85,000 relating to the implementation of ASU 2016-13 &#x201C;Measurement of Credit Losses on Financial</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Instruments.&#x201D;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;Audit services include the following: (1) professional services rendered for the audit of the Corporation&#x2019;s annual consolidated financial statements; (2) reviews of the consolidated financial statements included in the Corporation&#x2019;s Quarterly Reports on Form 10-Q; (3) a reading of the Corporation&#x2019;s Annual Report on Form 10-K; and (4) rendering an opinion on the effectiveness of the Corporation&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Audit Related Fees</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Audit </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">related fees, as described in Item 9(e)(2) of Schedule 14A of the SEC&#x2019;s Proxy Rules, are fees billed to the Corporation by its Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm (&#x201C;Independent Auditors&#x201D;) for assurance and related services that are reasonably related to the performance of the audit or review of the Corporation&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements and are not audit fees as described in the previous paragraph.&nbsp;&nbsp;In 2019</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and 2018</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, Crowe did not bill the Corporation for any audit related fees</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Cambria;color:#243F60;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">Tax Fees </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Crowe&#x2019;s </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">fees in 2019 and 2018 for preparing the Corporation&#x2019;s tax returns, providing tax advice and performing tax compliance work were $37,750 and $109,825, respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;Crowe&#x2019;s fees for 2018 include $78,825 for tax-related work, mainly the completion of a cost segregation study relating to accelerated tax depreciation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Cambria;color:#243F60;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">All Other Fees</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">neither of the last two fiscal years was the Corporation billed by Crowe for any fees other than those described above under the captions &#x201C;Audit Fees,&#x201D; &#x201C;Audit Related Fees&#x201D; and &#x201C;Tax Fees</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&#x201D;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Audit Committee Approval of Audit Related, Tax and Other Fees</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">2019 and 2018, the Audit Committee specifically approved or pre-approved all fees reported under the sections &#x201C;Audit Related Fees&#x201D; and &#x201C;Tax Fees</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&#x201D;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Engagement of Independent Auditors to Perform Audit Services and Non-Audit Services</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">On </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">an annual basis, and in accordance with the terms of written engagement letters, the Audit Committee has engaged the Corporation&#x2019;s Independent Auditors to perform audit services as previously defined and to prepare the Corporation&#x2019;s income tax returns</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">addition, from time to time the Audit Committee may engage the Corporation&#x2019;s Independent Auditors to perform non-audit services such as providing tax advice and performing tax compliance work.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Audit Committee will not engage the Independent Auditors to perform any non-audit service or pre-approve any non-audit service that could impair, in fact or appearance, the independence of the Independent Auditors.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, the Audit Committee will not pre-approve any non-audit service if such pre-approval constitutes delegation to management of the Audit Committee&#x2019;s responsibilities under the 1934 Act</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="AuditCommitteeReport"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">AUDIT COMMITTEE REPORT</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Under </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">its charter, the Audit Committee is responsible to assist</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the Board</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">in</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">fulfilling</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">its</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">oversight</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">responsibilities</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">by</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">reviewing and evaluating: 1) the qualifications and independence of the Independent Auditors; 2) the performance</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">of</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Corporation&#x2019;s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Independent Auditors, internal</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">audit function and vendors providing internal auditing services; 3) the integrity of the Corporation&#x2019;s financial statements; and 4) management&#x2019;s responsibilities to assure that there is in place an effective system of internal controls</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">While </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the Audit Committee has the responsibilities and powers set forth in this Charter, it is not the duty of the Audit Committee to plan or conduct audits or to determine that the Corporation&#x2019;s financial statements and disclosures are complete and accurate and are in accordance with Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (&#x201C;GAAP&#x201D;) and applicable rules and regulations.&nbsp;&nbsp;These are the responsibilities of management and the Independent Auditors</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Specific </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">duties and responsibilities of the Audit Committee include, among other things: 1) appoint, retain, compensate, evaluate and, where appropriate, replace the Independent Auditors;&nbsp;&nbsp;2) approve all fees and terms of engagement of the Independent Auditors; 3) confirm the independence of the Independent Auditors; 4) review and discuss with management and the Independent Auditors the Corporation&#x2019;s audited consolidated financial statements and internal control over financial reporting; 5) meet with the Corporation&#x2019;s Independent Auditors and review the scope of audit services and the results of their annual audit of the Corporation&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements, including any recommendations the Independent Auditors may have with respect to internal controls or other business matters; 6) approve the internal audit plan and review the scope and results of internal audits; 7) review the results of examinations performed by regulatory authorities; 8) oversee management&#x2019;s responsibility to fulfill the annual internal control reporting requirements of Section 404 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act and the annual audit and management reporting requirements of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation Improvement Act of 1991; 9) review the Bank's performance of its obligations under various laws and regulations, including those affecting consumers; 10) review related party transactions; and 11) oversee management&#x2019;s responsibility to </font>
		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">27</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">implement internal controls over information technology and information security risks</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">evaluation of the Independent Auditors occurs at least annually and includes, among other things, a review of the most recent Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (&#x201C;PCAOB&#x201D;) report and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">communications required by PCAOB Auditing Standard Number 1301 regarding the independence and appointment of the Independent Auditors and the results of the annual audit.&nbsp;&nbsp;The evaluation also includes consideration of the Independent Auditors qualifications and industry experience, the performance of the audit partner and audit team and the tenure of the firm and appropriateness of fees.&nbsp;&nbsp;Crowe has served as the Corporation&#x2019;s Independent Auditors since 2003 and the audit partner is rotated at least every five years.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Audit Committee received and reviewed the written disclosures and the letter from Crowe required by applicable requirements of the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">PCAOB</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> regarding Crowe&#x2019;s communications with the Audit Committee concerning independence, and discussed with Crowe their independence</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The </font><font style="display: inline;">Audit Committee reviews and discusses with management and the Independent Auditors the annual audited financial statements, the Annual Report on Form 10-K, Quarterly Reports on Form 10-Q and earnings press releases prior to their filing, including reviewing the disclosures made in "Management's Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations."&nbsp;&nbsp;The Audit Committee also reviews and discusses policies with respect to risk assessment and risk management.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such discussions include the Corporation&#x2019;s major financial and accounting risk exposures and the steps management has undertaken to control them</font><font style="display: inline;font-style:italic;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The </font><font style="display: inline;">Audit Committee reviews reports from management regarding, among other things, the framework and effectiveness of internal controls over financial reporting and disclosure controls, compliance with laws and regulations, and controls over information technology risk</font><font style="display: inline;">.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Audit Committee met eight times during 2019 and schedules meetings to ensure it devotes enough time and attention to the duties and responsibilities outlined in this report.&nbsp;&nbsp;Periodic executive sessions are held with the Independent Auditors, Chief Auditor and other members of management to discuss any matters that the Committee or these persons believe should be discussed</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Audit Committee regularly reports its activities to the Board, and annually conducts a review of its Charter and performs a self-assessment</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Based </font><font style="display: inline;">on the review and discussions referred to above, we recommended to the Board that the audited financial statements be included in the Corporation&#x2019;s Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December 31, 2019 for filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission</font><font style="display: inline;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The Audit Committee:</font>
		</p>

			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">preceding report shall not be deemed incorporated by reference by any general statement incorporating by reference this proxy statement into any filing under the 1933 Act or 1934 Act, except to the extent the Corporation specifically incorporates this information by reference, and shall not otherwise be deemed filed under the 1933 Act or the 1934 Act</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="OtherMatters"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">OTHER MATTERS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Board of the Corporation does not know of any matters for action by stockholders at the Annual Meeting other than the matters described in the Notice of Annual Meeting.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, the enclosed Proxy will confer discretionary authority with respect to matters which are not known to the Board at the time of the printing hereof and which may properly come before the meeting.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is the intention of the persons named in the proxy to vote such proxy with respect to such matters in accordance with their best judgment</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">entire expense of preparing, assembling and mailing the enclosed material will be borne by the Corporation.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to using the mail, directors, officers and employees of the Bank acting on behalf of the Corporation, and without extra compensation, may solicit proxies in person, by telephone or by facsimile</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="StckhldrsProposals"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">STOCKHOLDER PROPOSALS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Any </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">proposals of stockholders intended to be submitted at the 2021 Annual Meeting of Stockholders under SEC Rule 14a-8 must be </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">received by the Chairman of the Board or the President no </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">later than November 10, 2020 in order to</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> be considered for inclusion in the proxy statement and form of proxy for such meeting under SEC Rule 14a-8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Under </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">the Corporation&#x2019;s bylaws, a stockholder must follow certain procedures to nominate persons for election as directors or to introduce an item of business at a meeting of stockholders. These procedures provide, generally, that stockholders desiring to make nominations for directors, or to bring a proper subject of business before the 2021 Annual Meeting, must do so by a written notice timely delivered to the Corporation&#x2019;s Secretary generally not </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">later than December 10, 2020</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">28</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">If </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the Corporation is not notified of a matter to be brought before the 2021 Annual </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Meeting by December 10, 2020 or if</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> a matter is</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> omitted from the proxy statement or proxy pursuant to SEC Rule 14a-8, then the proxy may provide discretionary authority to management of the Corporation to vote against such matter</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Nothing </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">in this proxy statement will be deemed to require us to include in our proxy statement and proxy relating to an annual meeting any stockholder proposal that does not meet all of the requirements for inclusion established by the SEC in effect at the time such proposal is received</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
